member.remarks:
            The default behavior is:
            

 All void calls just return 

 Other Methods will return a default value (0 or null depending on the return type) 

 Properties will behave like simple properties. 
            


            
            Example of using Natural Mocks™ Return
            
            [Test]
            public void Test()
            {
            	// Start mocking 
                using (RecordExpectations recorder = RecorderManager.StartRecording())
                {
                   // CAUTION: ALL calls here are mocked!!!
                   // MyMethod will be mocked.
                   TestedClass.MyMethod();
                   recorder.ReturnDefaultImplementation();
                }
                
                // run our code, This will be mocked 
            	int actual = TestedClass.MyMethod();
                Assert.AreEqual(0,actual);
            	MockManager.Verify();
            }
            
            
